IV_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores initialization vector

H_MEM[%s].description: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

AAD_BLOCK_NUM.description: Additional Authential Data block number register

TEXT_IN.description: Stores the source data when the AES accelerator operates in the Typical AES working mode.

TEXT_OUT.description: Stores the result data when the AES accelerator operates in the Typical AES working mode.

MODE.description: Defines the key length and the encryption/decryption of the AES accelerator.

TRIGGER.description: Set this bit to 1 to start AES calculation.

STATE.description: Stores the working status of the AES accelerator. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

DMA_ENABLE.description: Defines the working mode of the AES accelerator. 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

BLOCK_MODE.description: Defines the block cipher mode of the AES accelerator operating under the DMA-AES working mode. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: reserved, 0x7: reserved.

BLOCK_NUM.description: Stores the Block Number of plaintext or ciphertext when the AES accelerator operates under the DMA-AES working mode.

INC_SEL.description: Defines the Standard Incrementing Function for CTR block operation. Set this bit to 0 or 1 to choose INC32 or INC128.

AAD_BLOCK_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

REMAINDER_BIT_NUM.description: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

CONTINUE.description: Set this bit to 1 to continue GCM operation.

INT_CLEAR.description: Set this bit to 1 to clear AES interrupt.

INT_ENA.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable AES interrupt and 0 to disable interrupt. This field is only effective for DMA-AES operation.

DATE.description: This bits stores the version information of AES.

DMA_EXIT.description: Set this bit to 1 to exit AES operation. This field is only effective for DMA-AES operation.

WRITEBACK_BYPASS.description: Set 1 to bypass cache writeback request to external memory so that spi will not check its attribute.

FLASH_PAGE_SIZE.description: Set the page size of the used MSPI flash. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

SRAM_PAGE_SIZE.description: Set the page size of the used MSPI external RAM. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

SARADC_WORK_MODE.description: 0: single mode, 1: double mode, 2: alternate mode

SARADC_SAR_SEL.description: 0: SAR1, 1: SAR2, only work for single SAR mode

SARADC_SAR_CLK_GATED.description: enable SAR CLK gate when saradc idle

SARADC_SAR1_PATT_P_CLEAR.description: clear the pointer of pattern table for DIG ADC1 CTRL

SARADC_SAR2_PATT_P_CLEAR.description: clear the pointer of pattern table for DIG ADC2 CTRL

SARADC_DATA_SAR_SEL.description: 1: sar_sel will be coded by the MSB of the 16-bit output data, in this case the resolution should not be larger than 11 bits.

SARADC_DATA_TO_I2S.description: 1: I2S input data is from SAR ADC (for DMA), 0: I2S input data is from GPIO matrix

SARADC_XPD_SAR_FORCE.description: force option to xpd sar blocks

SARADC_WAIT_ARB_CYCLE.description: wait arbit signal stable after sar_done

SARADC_MEAS_NUM_LIMIT.description: enable apb saradc limit the sample num

SARADC_SAR1_INV.description: 1: data to DIG ADC1 CTRL is inverted, otherwise not

SARADC_SAR2_INV.description: 1: data to DIG ADC2 CTRL is inverted, otherwise not

SARADC_XPD_WAIT.description: the cycle which saradc controller in xpd state

SARADC_RSTB_WAIT.description: the cycle which saradc controller in rst state

SARADC_STANDBY_WAIT.description: the cycle which saradc controller in standby state

ADC_ARB_APB_FORCE.description: adc2 arbiter force to enableapb controller

ADC_ARB_RTC_FORCE.description: adc2 arbiter force to enable rtc controller

ADC_ARB_WIFI_FORCE.description: adc2 arbiter force to enable wifi controller

THRES_ALL_EN.description: enable thres0 to monitor all channel

APB_ADC_EOF_NUM.description: the dma_in_suc_eof gen when sample cnt = spi_eof_num

CLK_SEL.description: Set this bit to enable clk_apll

IN_RST.description: This bit is used to reset DMA channel 0 Rx FSM and Rx FIFO pointer.

INDSCR_BURST_EN.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

IN_DATA_BURST_EN.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Rx channel 0 receiving data when accessing internal SRAM.

MEM_TRANS_EN.description: Set this bit 1 to enable automatic transmitting data from memory to memory via DMA.

DMA_INFIFO_FULL_THRS.description: This register is used to generate the INFIFO_FULL_WM_INT interrupt when Rx channel 0 received byte number in Rx FIFO is up to the value of the register.

IN_CHECK_OWNER.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

IN_EXT_MEM_BK_SIZE.description: Block size of Rx channel 0 when DMA access external SRAM. 0: 16 bytes      1: 32 bytes    2/3:reserved

IN_DONE.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0.

IN_SUC_EOF.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0. For UHCI0, the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

IN_ERR_EOF.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 0. For other peripherals, this raw interrupt is reserved.

IN_DSCR_ERR.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 0.

IN_DSCR_EMPTY.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Rx buffer pointed by inlink is full and receiving data is not completed, but there is no more inlink for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_FULL_WM.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when received data byte number is up to threshold configured by REG_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_THRS_CH0 in Rx FIFO of channel 0.

INFIFO_OVF_L1.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

INFIFO_UDF_L1.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

INFIFO_OVF_L3.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 3 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

INFIFO_UDF_L3.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 3 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

IN_SUC_EOF.description: Set this bit to clear the IN_SUC_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

INFIFO_UDF_L1.description: Set this bit to clear the INFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

INFIFO_FULL_L1.description: L1 Rx FIFO full signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_EMPTY_L1.description: L1 Rx FIFO empty signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_FULL_L2.description: L2 Rx FIFO full signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_EMPTY_L2.description: L2 Rx FIFO empty signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_FULL_L3.description: L3 Rx FIFO full signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_EMPTY_L3.description: L3 Rx FIFO empty signal for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_CNT_L1.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L1 Rx FIFO for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_CNT_L2.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L2 Rx FIFO for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_CNT_L3.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L3 Rx FIFO for Rx channel 0.

INFIFO_RDATA.description: This register stores the data popping from DMA FIFO.

INFIFO_POP.description: Set this bit to pop data from DMA FIFO.

INLINK_ADDR.description: This register stores the 20 least significant bits of the first inlink descriptor's address.

INLINK_AUTO_RET.description: Set this bit to return to current inlink descriptor's address, when there are some errors in current receiving data.

INLINK_STOP.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the inlink descriptors.

INLINK_START.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the inlink descriptors.

INLINK_RESTART.description: Set this bit to mount a new inlink descriptor.

INLINK_PARK.description: 1: the inlink descriptor's FSM is in idle state.  0: the inlink descriptor's FSM is working.

INLINK_DSCR_ADDR.description: This register stores the current inlink descriptor's address.

IN_SUC_EOF_DES_ADDR.description: This register stores the address of the inlink descriptor when the EOF bit in this descriptor is 1.

IN_ERR_EOF_DES_ADDR.description: This register stores the address of the inlink descriptor when there are some errors in current receiving data. Only used when peripheral is UHCI0.

INLINK_DSCR.description: The address of the current inlink descriptor x.

INLINK_DSCR_BF0.description: The address of the last inlink descriptor x-1.

INLINK_DSCR_BF1.description: The address of the second-to-last inlink descriptor x-2.

RX_PRI.description: The priority of Rx channel 0. The larger of the value, the higher of the priority.

PERI_IN_SEL.description: This register is used to select peripheral for Rx channel 0. 0:SPI2. 1: SPI3. 2: UHCI0. 3: I2S0. 4: I2S1. 5: LCD_CAM. 6: AES. 7: SHA. 8: ADC_DAC. 9: RMT.

OUT_RST.description: This bit is used to reset DMA channel 0 Tx FSM and Tx FIFO pointer.

OUT_AUTO_WRBACK.description: Set this bit to enable automatic outlink-writeback when all the data in tx buffer has been transmitted.

OUT_EOF_MODE.description: EOF flag generation mode when transmitting data. 1: EOF flag for Tx channel 0 is generated when data need to transmit has been popped from FIFO in DMA

OUTDSCR_BURST_EN.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 0 reading link descriptor when accessing internal SRAM.

OUT_DATA_BURST_EN.description: Set this bit to 1 to enable INCR burst transfer for Tx channel 0 transmitting data when accessing internal SRAM.

OUT_CHECK_OWNER.description: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

OUT_EXT_MEM_BK_SIZE.description: Block size of Tx channel 0 when DMA access external SRAM. 0: 16 bytes      1: 32 bytes    2/3:reserved

OUT_DONE.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been transmitted to peripherals for Tx channel 0.

OUT_EOF.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one outlink descriptor has been read from memory for Tx channel 0.

OUT_DSCR_ERR.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting outlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of outlink descriptor for Tx channel 0.

OUT_TOTAL_EOF.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data corresponding a outlink (includes one link descriptor or few link descriptors) is transmitted out for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L1.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Tx channel 0 is overflow.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L1.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Tx channel 0 is underflow.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L3.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 3 fifo of Tx channel 0 is overflow.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L3.description: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 3 fifo of Tx channel 0 is underflow.

OUT_DONE.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_DONE_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_EOF.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_DSCR_ERR.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_TOTAL_EOF.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L1.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUTFIFO_OVF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L1.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUTFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L3.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUTFIFO_OVF_L3_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L3.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the OUTFIFO_UDF_L3_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_DONE.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUT_DONE_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_EOF.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUT_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_DSCR_ERR.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_TOTAL_EOF.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L1.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUTFIFO_OVF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L1.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUTFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L3.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUTFIFO_OVF_L3_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L3.description: The interrupt enable bit for the OUTFIFO_UDF_L3_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_DONE.description: Set this bit to clear the OUT_DONE_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_EOF.description: Set this bit to clear the OUT_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_DSCR_ERR.description: Set this bit to clear the OUT_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT interrupt.

OUT_TOTAL_EOF.description: Set this bit to clear the OUT_TOTAL_EOF_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L1.description: Set this bit to clear the OUTFIFO_OVF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L1.description: Set this bit to clear the OUTFIFO_UDF_L1_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_OVF_L3.description: Set this bit to clear the OUTFIFO_OVF_L3_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_UDF_L3.description: Set this bit to clear the OUTFIFO_UDF_L3_CH_INT interrupt.

OUTFIFO_FULL_L1.description: L1 Tx FIFO full signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_EMPTY_L1.description: L1 Tx FIFO empty signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_FULL_L2.description: L2 Tx FIFO full signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_EMPTY_L2.description: L2 Tx FIFO empty signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_FULL_L3.description: L3 Tx FIFO full signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_EMPTY_L3.description: L3 Tx FIFO empty signal for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_CNT_L1.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L1 Tx FIFO for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_CNT_L2.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L2 Tx FIFO for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_CNT_L3.description: The register stores the byte number of the data in L3 Tx FIFO for Tx channel 0.

OUTFIFO_WDATA.description: This register stores the data that need to be pushed into DMA FIFO.

OUTFIFO_PUSH.description: Set this bit to push data into DMA FIFO.

OUTLINK_ADDR.description: This register stores the 20 least significant bits of the first outlink descriptor's address.

OUTLINK_STOP.description: Set this bit to stop dealing with the outlink descriptors.

OUTLINK_START.description: Set this bit to start dealing with the outlink descriptors.

OUTLINK_RESTART.description: Set this bit to restart a new outlink from the last address.

OUTLINK_PARK.description: 1: the outlink descriptor's FSM is in idle state.  0: the outlink descriptor's FSM is working.

OUTLINK_DSCR_ADDR.description: This register stores the current outlink descriptor's address.

OUT_EOF_DES_ADDR.description: This register stores the address of the outlink descriptor when the EOF bit in this descriptor is 1.

OUT_EOF_BFR_DES_ADDR.description: This register stores the address of the outlink descriptor before the last outlink descriptor.

OUTLINK_DSCR.description: The address of the current outlink descriptor y.

OUTLINK_DSCR_BF0.description: The address of the last outlink descriptor y-1.

OUTLINK_DSCR_BF1.description: The address of the second-to-last inlink descriptor x-2.

TX_PRI.description: The priority of Tx channel 0. The larger of the value, the higher of the priority.

PERI_OUT_SEL.description: This register is used to select peripheral for Tx channel 0. 0:SPI2. 1: SPI3. 2: UHCI0. 3: I2S0. 4: I2S1. 5: LCD_CAM. 6: AES. 7: SHA. 8: ADC_DAC. 9: RMT.

DMA_RAM_FORCE_PD.description: Set this bit to force power down DMA internal memory.

DMA_RAM_FORCE_PU.description: Set this bit to force power up DMA internal memory

DMA_RAM_CLK_FO.description: 1: Force to open the clock and bypass the gate-clock when accessing the RAM in DMA. 0: A gate-clock will be used when accessing the RAM in DMA.

AHBM_RST_INTER.description: Set this bit, then clear this bit to reset the internal ahb FSM.

AHBM_RST_EXTER.description: Set this bit, then clear this bit to reset the external ahb FSM.

ARB_PRI_DIS.description: Set this bit to disable priority arbitration function.

CLK_EN.description: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

IN_SIZE.description: This register is used to configure the size of L2 Tx FIFO for Rx channel 0. 0:16 bytes. 1:24 bytes. 2:32 bytes. 3: 40 bytes. 4: 48 bytes. 5:56 bytes. 6: 64 bytes. 7: 72 bytes. 8: 80 bytes.

OUT_SIZE.description: This register is used to configure the size of L2 Tx FIFO for Tx channel 0. 0:16 bytes. 1:24 bytes. 2:32 bytes. 3: 40 bytes. 4: 48 bytes. 5:56 bytes. 6: 64 bytes. 7: 72 bytes. 8: 80 bytes.

EXTMEM_REJECT_ADDR.description: This register store the first address rejected by permission control when accessing external RAM.

EXTMEM_REJECT_ATRR.description: The reject accessing. Bit 0: if this bit is 1, the rejected accessing is READ. Bit 1: if this bit is 1, the rejected accessing is WRITE.

EXTMEM_REJECT_CHANNEL_NUM.description: The register indicate the reject accessing from which channel.

EXTMEM_REJECT_PERI_NUM.description: This register indicate reject accessing from which peripheral.

EXTMEM_REJECT_INT_RAW.description: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when accessing external RAM is rejected by permission control.

EXTMEM_REJECT_INT_ST.description: The raw interrupt status bit for the EXTMEM_REJECT_INT interrupt.

EXTMEM_REJECT_INT_ENA.description: The interrupt enable bit for the EXTMEM_REJECT_INT interrupt.

EXTMEM_REJECT_INT_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the EXTMEM_REJECT_INT interrupt.

QUERY_KEY_WRONG.description: Checks the reason why DS_KEY is not ready

SET_START.description: Write 1 to this register to active the DS peripheral

SET_ME.description: Write 1 to this register to start DS operation.

SET_FINISH.description: Write 1 to this register to end DS operation.

QUERY_BUSY.description: Stores the status of the DS peripheral. 1: The DS peripheral is busy. 0: The DS peripheral is idle.

QUERY_KEY_WRONG.description: 1-15: HMAC was activated, but the DS peripheral did not successfully receive the DS_KEY from the HMAC peripheral. (The biggest value is 15). 0: HMAC is not activated.

MD_ERROR.description: MD checkout result. 1: The MD check fails. 0: The MD check passes.

PADDING_BAD.description: padding checkout result. 1: The padding check fails. 0: The padding check passes.

PGM_DATA0.description: Register 0 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA1.description: Register 1 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA2.description: Register 2 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA3.description: Register 3 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA4.description: Register 4 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA5.description: Register 5 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA6.description: Register 6 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA7.description: Register 7 that stores data to be programmed.

PGM_CHECK_VALUE0.description: Register 0 that stores the RS code to be programmed.

PGM_CHECK_VALUE1.description: Register 1 that stores the RS code to be programmed.

PGM_CHECK_VALUE2.description: Register 2 that stores the RS code to be programmed.

RD_REPEAT_ERR0.description: Programming error record register 0 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR1.description: Programming error record register 1 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR2.description: Programming error record register 2 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR3.description: Programming error record register 3 of BLOCK0.

RD_REPEAT_ERR4.description: Programming error record register 4 of BLOCK0.

RD_RS_ERR0.description: Programming error record register 0 of BLOCK1-10.

RD_RS_ERR1.description: Programming error record register 1 of BLOCK1-10.

WR_TIM_CONF1.description: Configurarion register 1 of eFuse programming timing parameters.

WR_TIM_CONF2.description: Configurarion register 2 of eFuse programming timing parameters.

PGM_DATA_0.description: The content of the 0th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_1.description: The content of the 1st 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_2.description: The content of the 2nd 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_3.description: The content of the 3rd 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_4.description: The content of the 4th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_5.description: The content of the 5th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_6.description: The content of the 6th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_DATA_7.description: The content of the 7th 32-bit data to be programmed.

PGM_RS_DATA_0.description: The content of the 0th 32-bit RS code to be programmed.

PGM_RS_DATA_1.description: The content of the 1st 32-bit RS code to be programmed.

PGM_RS_DATA_2.description: The content of the 2nd 32-bit RS code to be programmed.

RD_DIS.description: Set this bit to disable reading from BlOCK4-10.

DIS_RTC_RAM_BOOT.description: Set this bit to disable boot from RTC RAM.

DIS_ICACHE.description: Set this bit to disable Icache.

DIS_DCACHE.description: Set this bit to disable Dcache.

DIS_DOWNLOAD_ICACHE.description: Set this bit to disable Icache in download mode (boot_mode[3:0] is 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7).

DIS_DOWNLOAD_DCACHE.description: Set this bit to disable Dcache in download mode ( boot_mode[3:0] is 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7).

DIS_FORCE_DOWNLOAD.description: Set this bit to disable the function that forces chip into download mode.

DIS_USB.description: Set this bit to disable USB function.

DIS_CAN.description: Set this bit to disable CAN function.

SOFT_DIS_JTAG.description: Set these bits to disable JTAG in the soft way (odd number 1 means disable ). JTAG can be enabled in HMAC module.

DIS_PAD_JTAG.description: Set this bit to disable JTAG in the hard way. JTAG is disabled permanently.

DIS_DOWNLOAD_MANUAL_ENCRYPT.description: Set this bit to disable flash encryption when in download boot modes.

USB_DREFH.description: Controls single-end input threshold vrefh, 1.76 V to 2 V with step of 80 mV, stored in eFuse.

USB_DREFL.description: Controls single-end input threshold vrefl, 0.8 V to 1.04 V with step of 80 mV, stored in eFuse.

USB_EXCHG_PINS.description: Set this bit to exchange USB D+ and D- pins.

EXT_PHY_ENABLE.description: Set this bit to enable external PHY.

BTLC_GPIO_ENABLE.description: Bluetooth GPIO signal output security level control.

VDD_SPI_MODECURLIM.description: SPI regulator switches current limit mode.

VDD_SPI_TIEH.description: SPI regulator output is short connected to VDD3P3_RTC_IO.

VDD_SPI_FORCE.description: Set this bit and force to use the configuration of eFuse to configure VDD_SPI.

VDD_SPI_EN_INIT.description: Set SPI regulator to 0 to configure init[1:0]=0.

VDD_SPI_ENCURLIM.description: Set SPI regulator to 1 to enable output current limit.

VDD_SPI_DCURLIM.description: Tunes the current limit threshold of SPI regulator when tieh=0, about 800 mA/(8+d).

VDD_SPI_INIT.description: Adds resistor from LDO output to ground. 0: no resistance 1: 6 K 2: 4 K 3: 2 K.

WDT_DELAY_SEL.description: Selects RTC watchdog timeout threshold, in unit of slow clock cycle. 0: 40000. 1: 80000. 2: 160000. 3:320000.

SPI_BOOT_CRYPT_CNT.description: Set this bit to enable SPI boot encrypt/decrypt. Odd number of 1: enable. even number of 1: disable.

SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE0.description: Set this bit to enable revoking first secure boot key.

SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE1.description: Set this bit to enable revoking second secure boot key.

SECURE_BOOT_KEY_REVOKE2.description: Set this bit to enable revoking third secure boot key.

SECURE_BOOT_EN.description: Set this bit to enable secure boot.

SECURE_BOOT_AGGRESSIVE_REVOKE.description: Set this bit to enable revoking aggressive secure boot.

DIS_USB_JTAG.description: Set this bit to disable function of usb switch to jtag in module of usb device.

DIS_USB_DEVICE.description: Set this bit to disable usb device.

STRAP_JTAG_SEL.description: Set this bit to enable selection between usb_to_jtag and pad_to_jtag through strapping gpio10 when both reg_dis_usb_jtag and reg_dis_pad_jtag are equal to 0.

USB_PHY_SEL.description: This bit is used to switch internal PHY and external PHY for USB OTG and USB Device. 0: internal PHY is assigned to USB Device while external PHY is assigned to USB OTG. 1: internal PHY is assigned to USB OTG while external PHY is assigned to USB Device.

POWER_GLITCH_DSENSE.description: Sample delay configuration of power glitch.

FLASH_TPUW.description: Configures flash waiting time after power-up, in unit of ms. If the value is less than 15, the waiting time is the configurable value.  Otherwise, the waiting time is twice the configurable value.

DIS_DOWNLOAD_MODE.description: Set this bit to disable download mode (boot_mode[3:0] = 0, 1, 2, 3, 6, 7).

DIS_LEGACY_SPI_BOOT.description: Set this bit to disable Legacy SPI boot mode (boot_mode[3:0] = 4).

UART_PRINT_CHANNEL.description: Selectes the default UART print channel. 0: UART0. 1: UART1.

FLASH_ECC_MODE.description: Set ECC mode in ROM, 0: ROM would Enable Flash ECC 16to18 byte mode. 1:ROM would use 16to17 byte mode.

DIS_USB_DOWNLOAD_MODE.description: Set this bit to disable UART download mode through USB.

ENABLE_SECURITY_DOWNLOAD.description: Set this bit to enable secure UART download mode.

UART_PRINT_CONTROL.description: Set the default UARTboot message output mode. 00: Enabled. 01: Enabled when GPIO8 is low at reset. 10: Enabled when GPIO8 is high at reset. 11:disabled.

PIN_POWER_SELECTION.description: GPIO33-GPIO37 power supply selection in ROM code. 0: VDD3P3_CPU. 1: VDD_SPI.

FLASH_TYPE.description: Set the maximum lines of SPI flash. 0: four lines. 1: eight lines.

FLASH_ECC_EN.description: Set 1 to enable ECC for flash boot.

FORCE_SEND_RESUME.description: Set this bit to force ROM code to send a resume command during SPI boot.

SECURE_VERSION.description: Secure version (used by ESP-IDF anti-rollback feature).

POWERGLITCH_EN.description: Set this bit to enable power glitch function.

EFUSE_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: Set this bit to force eFuse SRAM into power-saving mode.

MEM_CLK_FORCE_ON.description: Set this bit and force to activate clock signal of eFuse SRAM.

EFUSE_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: Set this bit to force eFuse SRAM into working mode.

EN.description: Set this bit and force to enable clock signal of eFuse memory.

OP_CODE.description: 0x5A5A: Operate programming command 0x5AA5: Operate read command.

READ_CMD.description: Set this bit to send read command.

PGM_CMD.description: Set this bit to send programming command.

BLK_NUM.description: The serial number of the block to be programmed. Value 0-10 corresponds to block number 0-10, respectively.

DAC_CLK_DIV.description: Controls the division factor of the rising clock of the programming voltage.

OE_CLR.description: Reduces the power supply of the programming voltage.

READ_INIT_NUM.description: Configures the initial read time of eFuse.

PWR_ON_NUM.description: Configures the power up time for VDDQ.

DCACHE_ENABLE.description: The bit is used to activate the data cache. 0: disable, 1: enable

DCACHE_SIZE_MODE.description: The bit is used to configure cache memory size.0: 32KB, 1: 64KB

DCACHE_BLOCKSIZE_MODE.description: The bit is used to configure cache block size.0: 16 bytes, 1: 32 bytes,2: 64 bytes

DCACHE_SHUT_CORE0_BUS.description: The bit is used to disable core0 dbus, 0: enable, 1: disable

DCACHE_SHUT_CORE1_BUS.description: The bit is used to disable core1 dbus, 0: enable, 1: disable

DCACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_ON.description: The bit is used to close clock gating of dcache tag memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

DCACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: The bit is used to power dcache tag memory down, 0: follow  rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power down

DCACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: The bit is used to power dcache tag memory up, 0: follow  rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power up

DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_EN.description: The bit is used to enable the first section of prelock function.

DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_EN.description: The bit is used to enable the second section of prelock function.

DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR.description: The bits are used to configure the first start virtual address of data prelock, which is combined with DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE_REG

DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR.description: The bits are used to configure the second start virtual address of data prelock, which is combined with DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE_REG

DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE.description: The bits are used to configure the second length of data locking, which is combined with DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR_REG

DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE.description: The bits are used to configure the first length of data locking, which is combined with DCACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR_REG

DCACHE_LOCK_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable lock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after lock operation done.

DCACHE_UNLOCK_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable unlock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after unlock operation done.

DCACHE_LOCK_DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate unlock/lock operation is finished.

DCACHE_LOCK_ADDR.description: The bits are used to configure the start virtual address for lock operations. It should be combined with DCACHE_LOCK_SIZE_REG.

DCACHE_LOCK_SIZE.description: The bits are used to configure the length for lock operations. The bits are the counts of cache block. It should be combined with DCACHE_LOCK_ADDR_REG.

DCACHE_INVALIDATE_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after invalidate operation done.

DCACHE_WRITEBACK_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable writeback operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback operation done.

CORE1_IBUS_REJECT_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate interrupt by authentication fail.

CORE1_DBUS_ACS_MSK_DCACHE_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate interrupt by cpu access dcache while the core1_dbus is disabled or dcache is disabled which include speculative access.

CORE1_DBUS_REJECT_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate interrupt by authentication fail.

CORE0_DBUS_TAG_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of data from external memory when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able, 4: write-able.

CORE0_DBUS_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of CPU access dbus when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able, 4: write-able.

CORE0_DBUS_WORLD.description: The bit is used to indicate the world of CPU access dbus when authentication fail. 0: WORLD0, 1: WORLD1

CORE0_DBUS_VADDR.description: The bits are used to indicate the virtual address of CPU access dbus when authentication fail.

CORE0_IBUS_TAG_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of data from external memory when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able, 4: write-able.

CORE0_IBUS_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of CPU access ibus when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able

CORE0_IBUS_WORLD.description: The bit is used to indicate the world of CPU access ibus when authentication fail. 0: WORLD0, 1: WORLD1

CORE0_IBUS_VADDR.description: The bits are used to indicate the virtual address of CPU access  ibus when authentication fail.

CORE1_DBUS_TAG_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of data from external memory when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able, 4: write-able.

CORE1_DBUS_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of CPU access dbus when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able, 4: write-able.

CORE1_DBUS_WORLD.description: The bit is used to indicate the world of CPU access dbus when authentication fail. 0: WORLD0, 1: WORLD1

CORE1_DBUS_VADDR.description: The bits are used to indicate the virtual address of CPU access dbus when authentication fail.

CORE1_IBUS_TAG_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of data from external memory when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able, 4: write-able.

CORE1_IBUS_ATTR.description: The bits are used to indicate the attribute of CPU access ibus when authentication fail. 0: invalidate, 1: execute-able, 2: read-able

CORE1_IBUS_WORLD.description: The bit is used to indicate the world of CPU access ibus when authentication fail. 0: WORLD0, 1: WORLD1

CORE1_IBUS_VADDR.description: The bits are used to indicate the virtual address of CPU access  ibus when authentication fail.

CACHE_MMU_FAULT_CONTENT.description: The bits are used to indicate the content of mmu entry which cause mmu fault..

CACHE_MMU_FAULT_CODE.description: The right-most 3 bits are used to indicate the operations which cause mmu fault occurrence. 0: default, 1: cpu miss, 2: preload miss, 3: writeback, 4: cpu miss evict recovery address, 5: load miss evict recovery address, 6: external dma tx, 7: external dma rx. The most significant bit is used to indicate this operation occurs in which one icache.

CACHE_MMU_FAULT_VADDR.description: The bits are used to indicate the virtual address which cause mmu fault..

CACHE_FLASH_WRAP_AROUND.description: The bit is used to enable wrap around mode when read data from flash.

CACHE_SRAM_RD_WRAP_AROUND.description: The bit is used to enable wrap around mode when read data from spiram.

CACHE_MMU_MEM_FORCE_ON.description: The bit is used to enable clock gating to save power when access mmu memory, 0: enable, 1: disable

CACHE_MMU_MEM_FORCE_PD.description: The bit is used to power mmu memory down, 0: follow_rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power down

CACHE_MMU_MEM_FORCE_PU.description: The bit is used to power mmu memory down, 0: follow_rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power up

ICACHE_STATE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether  icache main fsm is in idle state or not. 1: in idle state,  0: not in idle state

DCACHE_STATE.description: The bit is used to indicate whether dcache main fsm is in idle state or not. 1: in idle state,  0: not in idle state

CLK_FORCE_ON_MANUAL_CRYPT.description: The bit is used to close clock gating of manual crypt clock. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

CLK_FORCE_ON_AUTO_CRYPT.description: The bit is used to close clock gating of automatic crypt clock. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

CLK_FORCE_ON_CRYPT.description: The bit is used to close clock gating of external memory encrypt and decrypt clock. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

ICACHE_PRELOAD_INT_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate the interrupt by  icache pre-load done.

ICACHE_PRELOAD_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the interrupt by  icache pre-load done.

ICACHE_PRELOAD_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the interrupt by  icache pre-load done.

DCACHE_PRELOAD_INT_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate the interrupt by dcache pre-load done.

DCACHE_PRELOAD_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the interrupt by dcache pre-load done.

DCACHE_PRELOAD_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the interrupt by dcache pre-load done.

ICACHE_SYNC_INT_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate the interrupt by  icache sync done.

ICACHE_SYNC_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the interrupt by  icache sync done.

ICACHE_SYNC_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the interrupt by  icache sync done.

DCACHE_SYNC_INT_ST.description: The bit is used to indicate the interrupt by dcache sync done.

DCACHE_SYNC_INT_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable the interrupt by dcache sync done.

DCACHE_SYNC_INT_CLR.description: The bit is used to clear the interrupt by dcache sync done.

CACHE_MMU_OWNER.description: The bits are used to specify the owner of MMU.bit0: icache, bit1: dcache, bit2: dma, bit3: reserved.

CACHE_IGNORE_PRELOAD_MMU_ENTRY_FAULT.description: The bit is used to disable checking mmu entry fault by preload operation.

CACHE_IGNORE_SYNC_MMU_ENTRY_FAULT.description: The bit is used to disable checking mmu entry fault by sync operation.

CACHE_TRACE_ENA.description: The bit is used to enable cache trace function.

ENA.description: The bit is used to enable dcache freeze mode

MODE.description: The bit is used to configure freeze mode, 0:  assert busy if CPU miss 1: assert hit if CPU miss

DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate dcache freeze success

ENA.description: The bit is used to enable icache freeze mode

MODE.description: The bit is used to configure freeze mode, 0:  assert busy if CPU miss 1: assert hit if CPU miss

DONE.description: The bit is used to indicate icache freeze success

ICACHE_ATOMIC_OPERATE_ENA.description: The bit is used to activate icache atomic operation protection. In this case, sync/lock operation can not interrupt miss-work. This feature does not work during invalidateAll operation.

DCACHE_ATOMIC_OPERATE_ENA.description: The bit is used to activate dcache atomic operation protection. In this case, sync/lock/occupy operation can not interrupt miss-work. This feature does not work during invalidateAll operation.

BYPASS.description: The bit is used to disable request recording which could cause performance issue

ICACHE_TAG_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set icache tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

DCACHE_TAG_OBJECT.description: Set this bit to set dcache tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

CACHE_TAG_WAY_OBJECT.description: Set this bits to select which way of the tag-object will be accessed. 0: way0, 1: way1, 2: way2, 3: way3, .., 7: way7.

CACHE_VADDR.description: Those bits stores the virtual address which will decide where inside the specified tag memory object will be accessed.

CACHE_TAG_CONTENT.description: This is a constant place where we can write data to or read data from the tag memory on the specified cache.

SYNC1_BYPASS.description: set GPIO input_sync1 signal mode. 0:disable. 1:trigger at negedge. 2or3:trigger at posedge.

INT_TYPE.description: set this value to choose interrupt mode. 0:disable GPIO interrupt. 1:trigger at posedge. 2:trigger at negedge. 3:trigger at any edge. 4:valid at low level. 5:valid at high level

IN_SEL.description: set this value: s=0-53: connect GPIO[s] to this port. s=0x38: set this port always high level. s=0x3C: set this port always low level.

IN_INV_SEL.description: set this bit to invert input signal. 1:invert. 0:not invert.

SEL.description: set this bit to bypass GPIO. 1:do not bypass GPIO. 0:bypass GPIO.

OUT_SEL.description: The value of the bits: 0<=s<=256. Set the value to select output signal. s=0-255: output of GPIO[n] equals input of peripheral[s]. s=256: output of GPIO[n] equals GPIO_OUT_REG[n].

INV_SEL.description: set this bit to invert output signal.1:invert.0:not invert.

OEN_SEL.description: set this bit to select output enable signal.1:use GPIO_ENABLE_REG[n] as output enable signal.0:use peripheral output enable signal.

OEN_INV_SEL.description: set this bit to invert output enable signal.1:invert.0:not invert.

CLK_EN.description: set this bit to enable GPIO clock gate

SCL_LOW_PERIOD.description:
Configures the low level width of the SCL
Clock

TO.description: Setting time out control for receiving data.

INT_STATUS.description: Status of captured I2C communication events

SDA_HOLD.description: Configures the hold time after a negative SCL edge.

SDA_SAMPLE.description: Configures the sample time after a positive SCL edge.

SCL_HIGH_PERIOD.description: Configures the high level width of SCL

SCL_START_HOLD.description: Configures the delay between the SDA and SCL negative edge for a start condition

SCL_RSTART_SETUP.description:
Configures the delay between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA

SCL_STOP_HOLD.description:
Configures the delay after the SCL clock
edge for a stop condition

SCL_STOP_SETUP.description:
Configures the delay between the SDA and
SCL positive edge for a stop condition

FILTER_CFG.description: SCL and SDA filter configuration register

SCL_MAIN_ST_TIME_OUT.description: SCL main status time out register

SCL_STRETCH_CONF.description: Set SCL stretch of I2C slave

SCL_LOW_PERIOD.description: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains low in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

SAMPLE_SCL_LEVEL.description:
This register is used to select the sample mode.
1: sample SDA data on the SCL low level.
0: sample SDA data on the SCL high level.

RX_FULL_ACK_LEVEL.description: This register is used to configure the ACK value that need to sent by master when the rx_fifo_cnt has reached the threshold.

MS_MODE.description:
Set this bit to configure the module as an I2C Master. Clear this bit to configure the
module as an I2C Slave.

TRANS_START.description: Set this bit to start sending the data in txfifo.

ARBITRATION_EN.description: This is the enable bit for arbitration_lost.

FSM_RST.description: This register is used to reset the scl FMS.

SLV_TX_AUTO_START_EN.description: This is the enable bit for slave to send data automatically

ADDR_10BIT_RW_CHECK_EN.description: This is the enable bit to check if the r/w bit of 10bit addressing consists with I2C protocol

ADDR_BROADCASTING_EN.description: This is the enable bit to support the 7bit general call function.

RESP_REC.description: The received ACK value in master mode or slave mode. 0: ACK, 1: NACK.

SLAVE_RW.description: When in slave mode, 1: master reads from slave; 0: master writes to slave.

ARB_LOST.description: When the I2C controller loses control of SCL line, this register changes to 1.

BUS_BUSY.description: 1: the I2C bus is busy transferring data; 0: the I2C bus is in idle state.

SLAVE_ADDRESSED.description:
When configured as an I2C Slave, and the address sent by the master is
equal to the address of the slave, then this bit will be of high level.

RXFIFO_CNT.description: This field represents the amount of data needed to be sent.

STRETCH_CAUSE.description: The cause of stretching SCL low in slave mode. 0:  stretching SCL low at the beginning of I2C read data state. 1: stretching SCL low when I2C Tx FIFO is empty in slave mode. 2: stretching SCL low when I2C Rx FIFO is full in slave mode.

TXFIFO_CNT.description: This field stores the amount of received data in RAM.

SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST.description:
This field indicates the states of the I2C module state machine. 
0: Idle; 1: Address shift; 2: ACK address; 3: Rx data; 4: Tx data; 5: Send ACK; 6: Wait ACK

SCL_STATE_LAST.description:
This field indicates the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.
0: Idle; 1: Start; 2: Negative edge; 3: Low; 4: Positive edge; 5: High; 6: Stop

TIME_OUT_VALUE.description:
This register is used to configure the timeout for receiving a data bit in APB
clock cycles.

TIME_OUT_EN.description: This is the enable bit for time out control.

SLAVE_ADDR.description: When configured as an I2C Slave, this field is used to configure the slave address.

ADDR_10BIT_EN.description: This field is used to enable the slave 10-bit addressing mode in master mode.

RXFIFO_RADDR.description: This is the offset address of the APB reading from rxfifo

RXFIFO_WADDR.description: This is the offset address of i2c module receiving data and writing to rxfifo.

TXFIFO_RADDR.description: This is the offset address of i2c module reading from txfifo.

TXFIFO_WADDR.description: This is the offset address of APB bus writing to txfifo.

SLAVE_RW_POINT.description: The received data in I2C slave mode.

RXFIFO_WM_THRHD.description: The water mark threshold of rx FIFO in nonfifo access mode. When reg_reg_fifo_prt_en is 1 and rx FIFO counter is bigger than reg_rxfifo_wm_thrhd[4:0], reg_rxfifo_wm_int_raw bit will be valid.

TXFIFO_WM_THRHD.description: The water mark threshold of tx FIFO in nonfifo access mode. When reg_reg_fifo_prt_en is 1 and tx FIFO counter is smaller than reg_txfifo_wm_thrhd[4:0], reg_txfifo_wm_int_raw bit will be valid.

NONFIFO_EN.description: Set this bit to enable APB nonfifo access.

FIFO_ADDR_CFG_EN.description: When this bit is set to 1, the byte received after the I2C address byte represents the offset address in the I2C Slave RAM.

RX_FIFO_RST.description: Set this bit to reset rx-fifo.

TX_FIFO_RST.description: Set this bit to reset tx-fifo.

FIFO_PRT_EN.description: The control enable bit of FIFO pointer in non-fifo access mode. This bit controls the valid bits and the interrupts of tx/rx_fifo overflow, underflow, full and empty.

FIFO_RDATA.description: The value of rx FIFO read data.

TIME.description:
This register is used to configure the time to hold the data after the negative
edge of SCL, in I2C module clock cycles.
This register is used to configure for how long SDA is sampled, in I2C module clock cycles.

SCL_HIGH_PERIOD.description: This register is used to configure for how long SCL remains high in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

SCL_WAIT_HIGH_PERIOD.description: This register is used to configure for the SCL_FSM's waiting period for SCL high level in master mode, in I2C module clock cycles.

TIME.description:
This register is used to configure the time between the negative edge
of SDA and the negative edge of SCL for a START condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

This register is used to configure the time between the positive
edge of SCL and the negative edge of SDA for a RESTART condition, in I2C module clock cycles.

This register is used to configure the delay after the STOP condition,
in I2C module clock cycles.

This register is used to configure the time between the positive edge
of SCL and the positive edge of SDA, in I2C module clock cycles.

SCL_FILTER_THRES.description:
When a pulse on the SCL input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

SDA_FILTER_THRES.description:
When a pulse on the SDA input has smaller width than this register value
in I2C module clock cycles, the I2C controller will ignore that pulse.

SCL_FILTER_EN.description: This is the filter enable bit for SCL.

SDA_FILTER_EN.description: This is the filter enable bit for SDA.

SCLK_DIV_NUM.description: the integral part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

SCLK_DIV_A.description: the numerator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

SCLK_DIV_B.description: the denominator of the fractional part of the fractional divisor for i2c module

SCLK_SEL.description: The clock selection for i2c module:0-XTAL;1-CLK_8MHz.

SCLK_ACTIVE.description: The clock switch for i2c module

COMMAND.description:
This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command, 0: RSTART; 1: WRITE; 2: READ; 3: STOP; 4: END.
Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more
Information.

COMMAND_DONE.description:
When command 0 is done in I2C Master mode, this bit changes to high
level.

SCL_ST_TO_I2C.description: The threshold value of SCL_FSM state unchanged period. It should be o more than 23

SCL_MAIN_ST_TO_I2C.description: The threshold value of SCL_MAIN_FSM state unchanged period.nIt should be o more than 23

SCL_RST_SLV_EN.description: When I2C master is IDLE, set this bit to send out SCL pulses. The number of pulses equals to reg_scl_rst_slv_num[4:0].

SCL_RST_SLV_NUM.description: Configure the pulses of SCL generated in I2C master mode. Valid when reg_scl_rst_slv_en is 1.

SCL_PD_EN.description: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SCL line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_scl_force_out and reg_scl_pd_en to 1 to stretch SCL low.

SDA_PD_EN.description: The power down enable bit for the I2C output SDA line. 1: Power down. 0: Not power down. Set reg_sda_force_out and reg_sda_pd_en to 1 to stretch SDA low.

STRETCH_PROTECT_NUM.description: Configure the period of I2C slave stretching SCL line.

SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_EN.description: The enable bit for slave SCL stretch function. 1: Enable. 0: Disable. The SCL output line will be stretched low when reg_slave_scl_stretch_en is 1 and stretch event happens. The stretch cause can be seen in reg_stretch_cause.

SLAVE_SCL_STRETCH_CLR.description: Set this bit to clear the I2C slave SCL stretch function.

SLAVE_BYTE_ACK_CTL_EN.description: The enable bit for slave to control ACK level function.

SLAVE_BYTE_ACK_LVL.description: Set the ACK level when slave controlling ACK level function enables.

DATE.description: This is the the version register.

TXFIFO_START_ADDR.description: This is the I2C txfifo first address.

RXFIFO_START_ADDR.description: This is the I2C rxfifo first address.

RX_RESET.description: Set this bit to reset receiver

RX_FIFO_RESET.description: Set this bit to reset Rx AFIFO

RX_START.description: Set this bit to start receiving data

RX_SLAVE_MOD.description: Set this bit to enable slave receiver mode

RX_MONO.description: Set this bit to enable receiver  in mono mode

RX_BIG_ENDIAN.description: I2S Rx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr. 0: low addr with low addr value.

RX_UPDATE.description: Set 1 to update I2S RX registers from APB clock domain to I2S RX clock domain. This bit will be cleared by hardware after update register done.

RX_MONO_FST_VLD.description: 1: The first channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.   0: The second channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.

RX_PCM_CONF.description: I2S RX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

RX_PCM_BYPASS.description: Set this bit to bypass Compress/Decompress module for received data.

RX_STOP_MODE.description: 0  : I2S Rx only stop when reg_rx_start is cleared.   1: Stop when reg_rx_start is 0 or in_suc_eof is 1.   2:  Stop I2S RX when reg_rx_start is 0 or RX FIFO is full.

RX_LEFT_ALIGN.description: 1: I2S RX left alignment mode. 0: I2S RX right alignment mode.

RX_24_FILL_EN.description: 1: store 24 channel bits to 32 bits. 0:store 24 channel bits to 24 bits.

RX_WS_IDLE_POL.description: 0: WS should be 0 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

RX_BIT_ORDER.description: I2S Rx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is received first. 0:big endian, the MSB is received first.

RX_TDM_EN.description: 1: Enable I2S TDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

RX_PDM_EN.description: 1: Enable I2S PDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

RX_PDM_SINC_DSR_16_EN.description: Configure the down sampling rate of PDM RX filter group1 module. 1: The  down sampling rate is 128. 0: down sampling rate is 64.

TX_RESET.description: Set this bit to reset transmitter

TX_FIFO_RESET.description: Set this bit to reset Tx AFIFO

TX_START.description: Set this bit to start transmitting data

TX_SLAVE_MOD.description: Set this bit to enable slave transmitter mode

TX_MONO.description: Set this bit to enable transmitter in mono mode

TX_CHAN_EQUAL.description: 1: The value of Left channel data is equal to the value of right channel data in I2S TX mono mode or TDM channel select mode. 0: The invalid channel data is reg_i2s_single_data in I2S TX mono mode or TDM channel select mode.

TX_BIG_ENDIAN.description: I2S Tx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr.  0: low addr with low addr value.

TX_UPDATE.description: Set 1 to update I2S TX registers from APB clock domain to I2S TX clock domain. This bit will be cleared by hardware after update register done.

TX_MONO_FST_VLD.description: 1: The first channel data value is valid in I2S TX mono mode.   0: The second channel data value is valid in I2S TX mono mode.

TX_PCM_CONF.description: I2S TX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

TX_PCM_BYPASS.description: Set this bit to bypass  Compress/Decompress module for transmitted data.

TX_STOP_EN.description: Set this bit to stop disable output BCK signal and WS signal when tx FIFO is emtpy

TX_LEFT_ALIGN.description: 1: I2S TX left alignment mode. 0: I2S TX right alignment mode.

TX_24_FILL_EN.description: 1: Sent 32 bits in 24 channel bits mode. 0: Sent 24 bits in 24 channel bits mode

TX_WS_IDLE_POL.description: 0: WS should be 0 when sending left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when sending left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

TX_BIT_ORDER.description: I2S Tx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is sent first. 0:big endian, the MSB is sent first.

TX_TDM_EN.description: 1: Enable I2S TDM Tx mode . 0: Disable.

TX_PDM_EN.description: 1: Enable I2S PDM Tx mode . 0: Disable.

TX_CHAN_MOD.description: I2S transmitter channel mode configuration bits.

SIG_LOOPBACK.description: Enable signal loop back mode with transmitter module and receiver module sharing the same WS and BCK signals.

RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH.description: The width of rx_ws_out in TDM mode is (I2S_RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[6:0] +1) * T_bck

RX_BCK_DIV_NUM.description: Bit clock configuration bits in receiver mode.

RX_BITS_MOD.description: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S receiver channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

RX_TDM_CHAN_BITS.description: The Rx bit number for each channel minus 1in TDM mode.

RX_MSB_SHIFT.description: Set this bit to enable receiver in Phillips standard mode

TX_TDM_WS_WIDTH.description: The width of tx_ws_out in TDM mode is (I2S_TX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[6:0] +1) * T_bck

TX_BCK_DIV_NUM.description: Bit clock configuration bits in transmitter mode.

TX_BITS_MOD.description: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S transmitter channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

TX_TDM_CHAN_BITS.description: The Tx bit number for each channel minus 1in TDM mode.

TX_MSB_SHIFT.description: Set this bit to enable transmitter in Phillips standard mode

TX_BCK_NO_DLY.description: 1: BCK is not delayed to generate pos/neg edge in master mode. 0: BCK is delayed to generate pos/neg edge in master mode.

RX_CLK_ACTIVE.description: I2S Rx module clock enable signal.

RX_CLK_SEL.description: Select I2S Rx module source clock. 0: no clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

MCLK_SEL.description: 0: UseI2S Tx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.  1: UseI2S Rx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.

TX_CLKM_DIV_NUM.description: Integral I2S TX clock divider value. f_I2S_CLK = f_I2S_CLK_S/(N+b/a). There will be (a-b) * n-div and b * (n+1)-div.  So the average combination will be:  for b <= a/2, z * [x * n-div + (n+1)-div] + y * n-div. For b > a/2, z * [n-div + x * (n+1)-div] + y * (n+1)-div.

TX_CLK_ACTIVE.description: I2S Tx module clock enable signal.

TX_CLK_SEL.description: Select I2S Tx module source clock. 0: XTAL clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

CLK_EN.description: Set this bit to enable clk gate

RX_CLKM_DIV_Z.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

RX_CLKM_DIV_Y.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

RX_CLKM_DIV_X.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

TX_CLKM_DIV_Z.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

TX_CLKM_DIV_Y.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

TX_CLKM_DIV_X.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1.description: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_TX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

TX_PDM_HP_BYPASS.description: I2S TX PDM bypass hp filter or not. The option has been removed.

TX_PDM_PRESCALE.description: I2S TX PDM prescale for sigmadelta

LCD_BK_EN.description: 1: Enable blank region when LCD sends data out. 0: No blank region.

LCD_CD_CMD_SET.description: 1: LCD_CD = !reg_cd_idle_edge when lcd_st[2:0] is in LCD_CMD state.  0: LCD_CD = reg_cd_idle_edge.

TIMER_SEL.description:
This field is used to select one of timers for channel %s.

0: select timer0

1: select timer1

2: select timer2

3: select timer3

SIG_OUT_EN.description: Set this bit to enable signal output on channel %s.

IDLE_LV.description: This bit is used to control the output value when channel %s is inactive (when LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s is 0).

PARA_UP.description: This bit is used to update LEDC_HPOINT_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_START_CH%s, LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s, LEDC_TIMER_SEL_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_NUM_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_SCALE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_INC_CH%s, and LEDC_OVF_CNT_EN_CH%s fields for channel %s, and will be automatically cleared by hardware.

OVF_NUM.description:
This register is used to configure the maximum times of overflow minus 1.

The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

OVF_CNT_EN.description: This bit is used to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

OVF_CNT_RESET.description: Set this bit to reset the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

OVF_CNT_RESET_ST.description: This is the status bit of LEDC_OVF_CNT_RESET_CH%s.

HPOINT.description: The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

DUTY.description:
This register is used to change the output duty by controlling the Lpoint.

The output value turns to low when the selected timers has reached the Lpoint.

DUTY_SCALE.description: This register is used to configure the changing step scale of duty on channel %s.

DUTY_CYCLE.description: The duty will change every LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s on channel %s.

DUTY_NUM.description: This register is used to control the number of times the duty cycle will be changed.

DUTY_INC.description: This register is used to increase or decrease the duty of output signal on channel %s. 1: Increase; 0: Decrease.

DUTY_START.description: Other configured fields in LEDC_CH%s_CONF1_REG will start to take effect when this bit is set to 1.

DUTY_R.description: This register stores the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

DUTY_RES.description: This register is used to control the range of the counter in timer %s.

CLK_DIV.description:
This register is used to configure the divisor for the divider in timer %s.

The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

PAUSE.description: This bit is used to suspend the counter in timer %s.

RST.description: This bit is used to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.

TICK_SEL.description:
This bit is used to select clock for timer %s. When this bit is set to 1 LEDC_APB_CLK_SEL[1:0] should be 1, otherwise the timer clock may be not accurate.

1'h0: SLOW_CLK 1'h1: REF_TICK

PARA_UP.description: Set this bit to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.

CNT.description: This register stores the current counter value of timer %s.

TIMER0_OVF_INT_RAW.description: Triggered when the timer0 has reached its maximum counter value.

TIMER1_OVF_INT_RAW.description: Triggered when the timer1 has reached its maximum counter value.

TIMER2_OVF_INT_RAW.description: Triggered when the timer2 has reached its maximum counter value.

TIMER3_OVF_INT_RAW.description: Triggered when the timer3 has reached its maximum counter value.

APB_CLK_SEL.description:
This bit is used to select clock source for the 4 timers .

2'd1: APB_CLK 2'd2: RTC8M_CLK 2'd3: XTAL_CLK

CLK_EN.description:
This bit is used to control clock.

1'b1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

DATE.description: This is the version control register.

FILTER_THRES.description:
This sets the maximum threshold, in APB_CLK cycles, for the filter.

Any pulses with width less than this will be ignored when the filter is enabled.

FILTER_EN.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's input filter.

THR_ZERO_EN.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's zero comparator.

THR_H_LIM_EN.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thr_h_lim comparator.

THR_L_LIM_EN.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thr_l_lim comparator.

THR_THRES0_EN.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thres0 comparator.

THR_THRES1_EN.description: This is the enable bit for unit %s's thres1 comparator.

CH0_NEG_MODE.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a negative edge.

1: Increase the counter;2: Decrease the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

CH0_POS_MODE.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a positive edge.

1: Increase the counter;2: Decrease the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

CH0_HCTRL_MODE.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CH0_LCTRL_MODE.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CH1_NEG_MODE.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a negative edge.

1: Increment the counter;2: Decrement the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

CH1_POS_MODE.description:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a positive edge.

1: Increment the counter;2: Decrement the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

CH1_HCTRL_MODE.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CH1_LCTRL_MODE.description:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

CNT_THRES0.description: This register is used to configure the thres0 value for unit %s.

CNT_H_LIM.description: This register is used to configure the thr_h_lim value for unit %s.

CNT_L_LIM.description: This register is used to configure the thr_l_lim value for unit %s.

ZERO_MODE.description: The pulse counter status of PCNT_U%s corresponding to 0. 0: pulse counter decreases from positive to 0. 1: pulse counter increases from negative to 0. 2: pulse counter is negative. 3: pulse counter is positive.

THRES1.description: The latched value of thres1 event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thres1 and thres1 event is valid. 0: others

THRES0.description: The latched value of thres0 event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thres0 and thres0 event is valid. 0: others

L_LIM.description: The latched value of low limit event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thr_l_lim and low limit event is valid. 0: others

H_LIM.description: The latched value of high limit event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thr_h_lim and high limit event is valid. 0: others

ZERO.description: The latched value of zero threshold event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to 0 and zero threshold event is valid. 0: others

CLK_EN.description: The registers clock gate enable signal of PCNT module. 1: the registers can be read and written by application. 0: the registers can not be read or written by application

DATE.description: This is the PCNT version control register.

CH%sDATA.description: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL%s by apb fifo access.

DATA.description: Read and write data for channel %s via APB FIFO.

TX_START.description: Set this bit to start sending data on CHANNEL%s.

MEM_RD_RST.description: Set this bit to reset read ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing transmitter.

APB_MEM_RST.description: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

TX_CONTI_MODE.description: Set this bit to restart transmission  from the first data to the last data in CHANNEL%s.

MEM_TX_WRAP_EN.description: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume sending at the start when the data to be sent is more than its memory size.

IDLE_OUT_LV.description: This bit configures the level of output signal in CHANNEL%s when the latter is in IDLE state.

IDLE_OUT_EN.description: This is the output enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s in IDLE state.

TX_STOP.description: Set this bit to stop the transmitter of CHANNEL%s sending data out.

DIV_CNT.description: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

MEM_SIZE.description: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

CARRIER_EFF_EN.description: 1: Add carrier modulation on the output signal only at the send data state for CHANNEL%s. 0: Add carrier modulation on the output signal at all state for CHANNEL%s. Only valid when RMT_CARRIER_EN_CH%s is 1.

CARRIER_EN.description: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

CARRIER_OUT_LV.description:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

DIV_CNT.description: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

IDLE_THRES.description: When no edge is detected on the input signal and continuous clock cycles is longer than this register value, received process is finished.

MEM_SIZE.description: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

CARRIER_EN.description: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

CARRIER_OUT_LV.description:
This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.

1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.

1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

RX_EN.description: Set this bit to enable receiver to receive data on CHANNEL%s.

MEM_WR_RST.description: Set this bit to reset write ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing receiver.

APB_MEM_RST.description: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

MEM_OWNER.description:
This register marks the ownership of CHANNEL%s's ram block.

1'h1: Receiver is using the ram. 

1'h0: APB bus is using the ram.

RX_FILTER_EN.description: This is the receive filter's enable bit for CHANNEL%s.

RX_FILTER_THRES.description: Ignores the input pulse when its width is smaller than this register value in APB clock periods (in receive mode).

MEM_RX_WRAP_EN.description: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume receiving at the start when the data to be received is more than its memory size.

MEM_RADDR_EX.description: This register records the memory address offset when transmitter of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

APB_MEM_WADDR.description: This register records the memory address offset when writes RAM over APB bus.

STATE.description: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

MEM_EMPTY.description: This status bit will be set when the data to be set is more than memory size and the wraparound mode is disabled.

APB_MEM_WR_ERR.description: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when writes via APB bus.

MEM_WADDR_EX.description: This register records the memory address offset when receiver of CHANNEL%s is using the RAM.

APB_MEM_RADDR.description: This register records the memory address offset when reads RAM over APB bus.

STATE.description: This register records the FSM status of CHANNEL%s.

MEM_OWNER_ERR.description: This status bit will be set when the ownership of memory block is wrong.

MEM_FULL.description: This status bit will be set if the receiver receives more data than the memory size.

APB_MEM_RD_ERR.description: This status bit will be set if the offset address out of memory size when reads via APB bus.
